  "prompt": "Can you confirm if money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is **illegal** in virtually all jurisdictions around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, or other crimes) appear legitimate by passing it through a complex sequence of transactions or financial systems. \n\n**Why is it illegal?**  \nMoney laundering is a criminal offense because it enables criminals to profit from illegal activities, undermines the integrity of financial systems, and can fuel further criminal behavior. Governments and international organizations, such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), have established strict laws and regulations to combat money laundering.\n\nIn many countries, penalties for money laundering include **heavy fines, asset seizure, and imprisonment**. Financial institutions and businesses are also required to implement anti-money laundering (AML) measures to detect and report suspicious activities.",
